**Design Decision Traceability:**

| Decision | Sprint/OQ | Implementation |
|----------|-----------|----------------|
| Tauri v2 (no Electron/Wails) | OQ-005/Sprint 69 | `src-tauri/`, `@tauri-apps/api@^2` |
| Svelte (not React) | ADR | `svelte@^4`, `App.svelte`, all `.svelte` components |
| CodeMirror 6 (no Monaco/Ace/ProseMirror) | ADR | `src/lib/editor/setup.ts`, `codemirror@^6` |
| Local .md only (no DB, no cloud) | Design doc | All I/O through `src-tauri/src/notes.rs` |
| YAML frontmatter with `tags` only | Design doc | `src/lib/frontmatter.ts`, `notes.rs::extract_tags` |
| Filename `YYYY-MM-DDTHHMMSS.md` with `_N` suffix | Design doc | `notes.rs::generate_filename` |
| SPA via `currentView` (no router lib) | Design doc | `src/lib/stores.ts::currentView`, `App.svelte` |
| 500ms auto-save debounce | OQ-004/Sprint 68 | `src/lib/editor/autosave.ts` |
| CSS Columns masonry | OQ-003/Sprint 67 | `GridView.svelte::masonry-grid` |
| Default 7-day filter | Design doc | `date-utils.ts::getDefaultDateRange(7)` |
| `navigator.clipboard.writeText` + execCommand fallback | Design doc | `src/lib/clipboard.ts` |
| `Cmd+N` / `Ctrl+N` for new note | Design doc | `src/lib/editor/keymaps.ts` (Mod-n) |
| StateField + Decoration for frontmatter | OQ-002/Sprint 66 | `src/lib/editor/frontmatter-decoration.ts` |
| 300ms search debounce | OQ-GRID-001 | `GridView.svelte::debouncedSearch` |
| Toast for error notification | OQ-006/Sprint 70 | `ToastContainer.svelte`, `stores.ts::addToast` |
| Linux + macOS only | Design doc | Tauri targets GTK WebKitGTK + WKWebView |

**Import Resolution Verification:**

All cross-file imports resolve within the `src/` tree:
- `$lib/*` → `src/lib/*` (via vite alias + tsconfig paths)
- Components import from `../lib/` (types, api, stores, utils)
- Editor modules import from `../` (debounce, frontmatter)
- `@tauri-apps/api/core` → `invoke()` for IPC
- `@tauri-apps/plugin-dialog` → directory picker in Settings
- `@codemirror/*` → CM6 packages for editor setup
- `svelte`, `svelte/store`, `svelte/transition` → Svelte runtime

**Build Commands:**
```bash
# Install dependencies
npm install

# Dev mode (frontend + Tauri)
npm run tauri dev

# Production build
npm run tauri build

# Frontend only (for testing)
npm run dev
